cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper proposes a new approach to modeling prediction uncertainty in neural networks using the theory of subjective logic. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on deep learning and classification problems, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
